                            <msItem xml:id="p1_i1">
                                <locus target="#2v"/>
                                <title type="complete" cert="medium" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3860KingList">Genealogy and chronology of the Ethiopian kings from
                                    <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1386Adam">Adam</persName> till <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5616IyasuI">ʾIyāsu I</persName>.</title>
                            <note>
                           <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/T6UTP6JE"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Turaev1906rukopisi"/><title level="m">Ėfiopskija rukopisi v S.-Peterburgě</title><title level="s">Pamjatniki ėfiopskoj pis'mennosti</title><author><forename>Boris</forename><surname>Turaev</surname></author><pubPlace>St Petersburg</pubPlace><publisher>Tipografija imperatorskoj Akademii Nauk</publisher><date>1906</date><series><title level="s">Pamjatniki ėfiopskoj pis'mennosti</title><biblScope unit="volume">3</biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">3</biblScope><note type="url">http://digitale-sammlungen.ulb.uni-bonn.de/content/titleinfo/2104581</note><note type="tags"><note type="tag">Manuscripts</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">bm:Turaev1906rukopisi</note></note><note type="tag">Manuscripts</note><note type="tag">Cataloguing</note><note type="tag">bm:Turaev1906rukopisi</note><citedRange unit="page">86-87</citedRange></bibl>writes that the names in this list differ from the 'normal' ones, he point to the similarity with <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet149">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien 149</ref>
                                and with the manuscript 22, f. 183v, which cannot be identified.
                          He also notes that <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFet149">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien 149</ref> often has <foreign xml:lang="gez">ታ</foreign> istead of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፓ</foreign> in the present manuscript</note>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="p1_i2">
                                <locus target="#3r"/>
