                        <msContents>
                            <msItem xml:id="p2_i1">
                                <locus from="17r" to="48v"/>
                                <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3141Hassab">Maṣḥafa ḥassāb</title>
                                <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                                <note>The text lacks title, and begins with the first verses from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1693John">Gospel of John</ref> and from <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1546Genesi">Genesis</ref>.
                               The text contains calender and astronomic instructions, and many tables: nineteen tables on <locus from="19r" to="31r"/>, seven tables with eight columns each on <locus from="41r" to="42v"/>
                              containing plinthium, lunar circle, new moon, epact, beginning of the lent, Jewish Easter, its week day, Christian Easter; on <locus target="#43r"/>there is a table of the month;
                            on <locus from="36r" to="36v"> </locus>there is a table with seven columns with the same content as on<locus from="41r" to="42v"/> for a cycle of nineteen years, for each week day starting from Wednesday.
                          On <locus target="#47v"/> there is a table with seven concentric cycles divided into twelve parts with radius. These parts are called <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማኅፈድ፡</foreign> (pillar) of each zodiac sign,
                        the circles are called <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰረገላ፡</foreign> (chariot).</note>
                            </msItem>
